# Include All Rules in Every Plan

## Core Rule

**When creating a plan in Plan mode, you MUST review ALL workspace rules in `.cursor/rules/` and incorporate them into your plan. No exceptions.**

## Process

1. Before creating any plan, read ALL `.mdc` files in `.cursor/rules/`
2. Check if any rules apply to the code you'll be modifying
3. Incorporate those rules' requirements into the plan
4. Reference the specific rules in the plan

## Why This Matters

Rules exist because patterns were broken before. If you don't check rules before planning, you'll repeat the same mistakes and waste the user's time.

## Example

User asks: "Add a new feature to the card component"

**Before writing the plan:**
1. Read `.cursor/rules/never-add-unrequested-features.mdc`
2. Read `.cursor/rules/restart-app-after-changes.mdc`
3. Read any other relevant rules

**In the plan:**
- Note: "Following never-add-unrequested-features.mdc - only implementing requested feature, no additional improvements"
- Note: "Following restart-app-after-changes.mdc - will rebuild and restart app after changes"

## No Exceptions

Even for "quick fixes" or "simple changes" - always check the rules first.
